17:29.355 --> 17:30.941
♪ Oh, glorious day ♪

17:31.081 --> 17:32.996
<i>You reached J. Leave a message.</i>
[ Touchscreen clicks ]

17:33.043 --> 17:34.706
[ Birds chirping ]

17:35.589 --> 17:37.784
♪♪

17:37.884 --> 17:40.405
♪ All mercy ♪

17:40.594 --> 17:42.954
♪ All goodness ♪

17:43.387 --> 17:46.159
♪ All beauty ♪

17:46.300 --> 17:49.011
♪ All wisdom ♪

17:49.151 --> 17:50.994
♪ All wonder ♪

17:51.394 --> 17:53.253
♪ is yours ♪

17:53.464 --> 17:55.823
- ♪ it is yours ♪
- put some money in.

17:56.019 --> 17:57.378
It's coming right back to us.

17:57.480 --> 18:01.355
♪♪

18:01.956 --> 18:06.058
Now I'd like our youth groups
to present their gifts.

18:06.322 --> 18:08.558
I know you've worked so hard,

18:08.784 --> 18:10.823
and you deserve
to be recognized.

18:10.927 --> 18:12.776
Let's hear it for them!

18:12.984 --> 18:16.284
[ Cheers and applause ]

18:16.331 --> 18:18.675
♪♪

18:20.557 --> 18:22.987
♪ All mercy ♪

18:23.394 --> 18:25.924
♪ All goodness ♪

18:26.043 --> 18:29.230
[ vehicle approaching ]

18:43.079 --> 18:45.263
[ Air brakes hiss ]

18:53.356 --> 18:58.186
I am thrilled to announce
that during this mission drive,

18:58.389 --> 19:00.389
thanks to your generosity,

19:00.525 --> 19:05.342
we have raised over $335,000

19:06.303 --> 19:10.033
for our hospital in Angola!
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:10.256 --> 19:14.506
And that's all before adding in
today's offerings!

19:14.647 --> 19:18.405
[ Cheers and applause continue ]

19:18.678 --> 19:22.272
You all have
a lot to be proud of.

19:22.725 --> 19:25.856
And I am so truly humbled

19:26.202 --> 19:27.702
to be your pastor.

19:28.225 --> 19:31.710
With the peace of the lord
and the grace of God,

19:31.764 --> 19:32.849
go out into the world

19:32.897 --> 19:36.506
and continue to do
great things in Jesus' name!

19:36.678 --> 19:38.235
Amen!

19:38.335 --> 19:40.350
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:40.592 --> 19:42.271
(Pastor:) Oh, yeah!

19:42.530 --> 19:46.085
♪♪

19:46.210 --> 19:50.331
[ woman singing indisttinctly ]

19:50.503 --> 19:53.573
[ Music continues, muffled ]

19:57.420 --> 20:00.520
♪♪

20:10.968 --> 20:13.866
[ sighs ]
[ Stall locks ]

20:19.059 --> 20:20.505
Whoo!

20:21.020 --> 20:23.926
Welcome, everyone.
Today is a great day, isn't it?

20:24.059 --> 20:25.505
Yeah, it is.

20:25.864 --> 20:26.942
With all that money,

20:27.012 --> 20:29.137
the mission trip can fly
first class, yeah?

20:29.192 --> 20:30.192
[ Laughter ]

20:30.247 --> 20:32.637
Amy, is it too late
for me to volunteer?

20:32.733 --> 20:34.037
I'm so sorry, Leon.

20:34.085 --> 20:36.725
I think the, uh, four seasons
Angola is all booked up.

20:36.780 --> 20:38.762
Maybe next year.
[ Laughter ]

20:45.769 --> 20:49.340
[ Faucet running ]

20:49.607 --> 20:51.007
[ Meter beeps ]

20:51.208 --> 20:52.544
[ Paper rustles ]

20:52.677 --> 20:56.356
[ Toilet flushing ]

20:56.596 --> 20:58.396
[ Faucet running ]

20:58.965 --> 21:01.301
[ Door opens, closes ]

21:01.684 --> 21:03.778
(Amy:) Do you have an example you
could share? [ Cellphone vibrates ]

21:03.825 --> 21:05.762
(Man:) Uh... No.

21:05.887 --> 21:07.559
That's okay. That's okay.

21:07.637 --> 21:10.153
Who else has a thought to share?

21:10.761 --> 21:12.394
- Excuse me.
- Come on.

21:12.442 --> 21:14.480
I feel like you have a thought
to share. I can see it.

21:14.528 --> 21:17.723
♪♪

21:18.019 --> 21:19.520
[ door opens ]

21:20.071 --> 21:21.538
(Pope:) Hallway's clear.

21:21.637 --> 21:23.239
[ Doors unlock ]

21:23.465 --> 21:25.795
♪♪

21:25.989 --> 21:29.143
[ drill whirring ]

21:32.082 --> 21:35.762
♪♪

21:41.591 --> 21:44.192
[ drill whirring ]

21:45.036 --> 21:46.397
[ Whispers ]
It's freezing in here.

21:46.567 --> 21:48.942
(Baz:) [ Whispers ] Quiet.
Sound carries.

21:49.100 --> 21:52.770
[ Drill whirring ]

21:56.897 --> 21:59.005
(Woman:) Oh, I didn't know
you were here today.

21:59.090 --> 22:01.943
(Man:) Hey, Sharon, yeah...
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

22:02.137 --> 22:03.576
[ Indistinct conversation ]

22:04.012 --> 22:06.349
[ Door opens, closes ]

22:06.419 --> 22:09.120
(Woman:) You, too. Bye.

22:29.039 --> 22:32.339
♪♪

22:48.581 --> 22:50.612
[ breathing heavily ]

22:52.481 --> 22:55.105
Whoever did the recon
on the hvac unit screwed up.

22:55.283 --> 22:57.151
<i>I can hear you, asshole.</i>

22:57.402 --> 23:00.003
It's "unseasonably warm" today.

23:00.380 --> 23:01.780
Prick.

23:02.273 --> 23:05.583
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:06.437 --> 23:10.219
♪♪

23:14.655 --> 23:17.140
Money's movin'.

23:30.687 --> 23:32.179
[ Lock cranks ]

23:32.304 --> 23:33.836
[ Clack ]

23:34.026 --> 23:37.196
♪♪

23:48.422 --> 23:51.547
Okay. Money's in the safe.

23:54.091 --> 23:57.431
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:07.959 --> 24:09.436
(Man:) Deliver us from evil.

24:09.484 --> 24:12.287
(All:) The kingdom, the power,
the glory are yours

24:12.482 --> 24:15.640
now and forever, amen.

24:16.427 --> 24:19.539
A perfect end
to an incredible day.

24:19.710 --> 24:21.484
See you all next week.

24:21.986 --> 24:25.086
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:25.465 --> 24:28.425
(Woman:) Oh, one other thing
I wanna share with you....

24:28.826 --> 24:31.054
(Man:) Good meeting.
See you next week.

24:31.160 --> 24:32.530
All right, see ya next week.

24:32.633 --> 24:35.360
[ Amy speaks indistinctly ]

24:35.539 --> 24:38.666
♪♪

24:47.845 --> 24:50.970
- (Amy:) [ Whispers ] See ya.
- Bye, bye, bye, bye.

24:55.592 --> 24:57.087
You comin'?

24:57.320 --> 25:00.320
Yeah, just finishin' up here.

25:02.364 --> 25:04.110
Where do you wanna go
for dinner?

25:04.241 --> 25:05.556
Um...

25:06.155 --> 25:08.962
Actually, I was thinking
we go back to my place

25:09.073 --> 25:11.048
and order takeout.

25:12.911 --> 25:14.642
Somethin' wrong?

25:15.206 --> 25:16.774
Um...

25:19.285 --> 25:21.235
Can I talk to you for a second?

25:22.235 --> 25:23.767
Yeah.

25:24.446 --> 25:26.454
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
What's the matter?

25:26.551 --> 25:30.321
When you were
sayin' earlier that...

25:31.307 --> 25:34.467
You were gonna reward me
for helping out...

25:37.618 --> 25:39.899
You meant sex, right?

25:41.056 --> 25:42.501
Sex.

25:52.264 --> 25:53.819
Come on, Pope.

25:53.889 --> 25:56.328
[ Sighs ] Jesus.
It's freezing in here.

25:56.448 --> 25:58.115
[ Whispers ] Shut up!

25:58.249 --> 26:00.296
[ Exhales sharply ]

26:02.502 --> 26:04.983
I never meant to make you
feel uncomfortable.

26:05.171 --> 26:07.811
If you don't want things
to get physical between us,

26:08.116 --> 26:09.913
they don't have to.

26:10.148 --> 26:12.249
Who says I don't want to?

26:14.779 --> 26:16.202
Sex before marriage is wrong.

26:16.334 --> 26:18.108
That's not who I am now.

26:18.358 --> 26:19.460
But that doesn't mean

26:19.508 --> 26:21.718
that I don't want
to feel close to you.

26:21.830 --> 26:23.760
There are things we <i> can</i> do

26:23.822 --> 26:25.742
that aren't necessarily...
[ Knock on doorframe ]

26:25.825 --> 26:28.069
Excuse me. I'm sorry.
I gotta lock up.

26:28.276 --> 26:29.904
No problem.

26:35.186 --> 26:37.569
<i>- I'm sorry we kept you so late.
- No, it's cool.</i>

26:37.755 --> 26:39.615
How many days
do you work this week?

26:39.772 --> 26:41.578
Um... [ sighs ]
Every day.

26:41.626 --> 26:42.890
Every day?
You have a 1-year-old, right?

26:42.977 --> 26:45.667
- I do.
- A girl?

26:45.838 --> 26:47.797
Yeah, a little girl.
I have to use the restroom.

26:47.845 --> 26:49.263
Oh, yeah.
I'll see you out there.

26:49.311 --> 26:51.871
- She look like you?
- She does.

26:55.439 --> 26:58.739
♪♪

27:01.526 --> 27:03.226
[ keys jingle ]

27:05.936 --> 27:07.702
[ Key snaps ]

27:08.252 --> 27:11.552
♪♪

27:14.791 --> 27:17.655
(Deran:)
Pope is out. Pope is out.

27:18.694 --> 27:20.366
[ Whispers ] Let's go.

27:25.481 --> 27:26.841
[ Thud ]

27:27.457 --> 27:29.622
[ Blows air ]

27:30.059 --> 27:31.934
[ Window whirs ] What are you doin' here?
Get out of here.

27:31.981 --> 27:33.348
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- Get out of here.

27:33.395 --> 27:35.579
- I-I want back in.
- No, no. Are you crazy?

27:35.653 --> 27:36.403
Get out of here.
Just open the door...

27:36.451 --> 27:37.677
get the hell out of here.
What is wrong with you?

27:37.724 --> 27:40.072
How much coke have you done?
Not that much. Hey, just...

27:40.261 --> 27:41.730
stop. Stop it, Craig.
Come on, man.

27:41.819 --> 27:43.840
Get the hell out of here, Craig.

27:46.423 --> 27:48.688
[ Metal squeaks and thuds ]

27:49.694 --> 27:51.764
[ Exhales sharply ]

27:54.164 --> 27:57.274
♪♪

28:04.441 --> 28:06.753
[ fabric rips ]
Oh, shit.

28:07.206 --> 28:08.620
[ Grunts ]

28:12.289 --> 28:14.519
[ Whispers ]
Okay, we're here. Do it now.

28:16.607 --> 28:17.642
You copy?

28:17.690 --> 28:20.456
Don't, man! Get the hell
out of here, man!

28:21.292 --> 28:22.510
What is wrong with you?

28:22.558 --> 28:24.620
What is wrong with you?! Huh?

28:24.862 --> 28:26.586
Get the hell out of here,
or you're gonna get us

28:26.633 --> 28:28.964
all thrown in prison.

28:29.967 --> 28:32.331
Can you hear me? Do it now.

28:32.476 --> 28:34.355
I'm going now.

28:35.571 --> 28:37.238
[ Engine starts ]

28:37.341 --> 28:39.058
[ Tires peal ]

28:39.390 --> 28:42.490
[ Engine revs ]

28:49.270 --> 28:51.200
(Deran:) Go now! Go now!

28:57.218 --> 28:58.878
[ Sneakers squeak ]

29:00.330 --> 29:01.930
[ Hiss ]

29:02.766 --> 29:05.709
(John:) I got a hit and run
over here at gate B.

29:08.672 --> 29:12.612
♪♪

29:13.863 --> 29:16.410
[ whispers ] J, what are you
doing? Get down here!

29:17.371 --> 29:19.847
[ Groaning ]

29:24.254 --> 29:25.855
J! Let's go, let's go!

29:25.956 --> 29:27.839
I can't. I'm stuck.

29:33.988 --> 29:36.996
[ Exhales ] Something's cutting
into my leg.

29:37.175 --> 29:38.347
[ Inhales sharply, groans ]

29:38.395 --> 29:40.816
Stop moving. Relax.
See if you can ease off of it.

29:40.988 --> 29:42.197
[ Exhales slowly ]

29:42.621 --> 29:43.833
Can you move now?

29:44.208 --> 29:45.575
[ Exhales sharply ]

29:46.375 --> 29:48.699
- No?
- No, nothin'. [Inhales sharply ]

29:48.840 --> 29:50.527
Okay, when I count to three...

29:50.705 --> 29:52.505
No!
[ Fabric rips ]

29:54.072 --> 29:57.542
[ Breathing heavily ]
[ Coughs ]

29:57.590 --> 29:58.721
Oh, shit.

29:58.879 --> 30:02.371
[ Inhales sharply ]
Oh, no. [ Groans ]

30:03.920 --> 30:05.865
Here. Stop the bleeding.

30:05.951 --> 30:07.865
W-what about...
what about the blood?

30:08.036 --> 30:09.982
- Are you in the database?
- What?

30:10.030 --> 30:11.730
Your DNA.
Is it in the database?

30:11.888 --> 30:14.158
Uh, no. Okay, then don't worry about it.
Let's go.

30:14.574 --> 30:17.264
[ Tape stretching ]

30:17.441 --> 30:20.011
[ Grunting ] Ah.

30:25.081 --> 30:28.351
♪♪

30:29.679 --> 30:32.249
[ heavy thuds ]

30:41.331 --> 30:44.771
[ Spraying ]

30:58.081 --> 31:01.181
♪♪

31:08.926 --> 31:11.226
[ engine starts ]

31:23.758 --> 31:25.602
(Baz:) [ Muffled voice ]
Go for it.

31:28.044 --> 31:31.047
[ Jackhammer whirring ]

31:32.515 --> 31:35.945
♪♪

31:38.828 --> 31:40.828
[ whirring continues ]

31:41.792 --> 31:43.962
Yeah, we're good.

31:45.361 --> 31:48.461
[ Whirring continues ]

32:00.143 --> 32:02.361
We got the security guard here
talkin' to the cops.

32:02.432 --> 32:03.674
I can still get around back.

32:03.722 --> 32:05.080
[ Whirs ]

32:13.244 --> 32:15.096
[ Clanking ]

32:16.178 --> 32:18.205
♪♪

32:18.314 --> 32:19.361
Okay, Okay.

32:19.409 --> 32:21.869
I got the security guard
heading back to the monitors.

32:32.104 --> 32:33.874
[ Door closes ]

32:35.900 --> 32:37.199
That's weird.

32:41.925 --> 32:43.058
[ Static ]

32:43.252 --> 32:44.496
(John:)<i> Scotty.</i>

32:47.368 --> 32:49.430
<i>Can you go check the camera
in the inventory room?</i>

32:49.530 --> 32:51.438
<i>I lost picture.</i>
[ Clank ]

32:51.796 --> 32:55.196
[ Thuds ]

32:57.534 --> 32:59.074
[ Cranking ]

32:59.512 --> 33:00.656
[ Thud ]

33:03.107 --> 33:04.578
[ Muffled ] Here we go.

33:17.616 --> 33:20.530
Is this the right key?
What's going on here?

33:23.967 --> 33:25.217
[ Bang ]

33:31.365 --> 33:32.647
[ Metal scrapes ]

33:41.044 --> 33:42.757
(Baz:) We're on the move.
Bring it around.

33:42.896 --> 33:44.514
<i>Yeah, coming now.</i>

33:52.555 --> 33:55.855
♪♪

33:57.208 --> 33:58.764
All right, go, go, go, go, go.

34:05.687 --> 34:07.617
[ Tires peal ]

34:12.208 --> 34:15.308
♪♪

34:26.281 --> 34:28.051
Oh!

34:30.157 --> 34:31.539
I don't think this is
gonna work, man.

34:31.585 --> 34:33.822
No, it will.
Just keep droppin'...

34:33.945 --> 34:35.188
drop it a few more times.

34:35.273 --> 34:36.993
You gotta wait until
the locking rods break.

34:37.078 --> 34:38.389
- You got that blowtorch, yeah?
- I'll get the blowtorch.

34:38.437 --> 34:41.367
No, no, you can't burn through it.
It's craton.

34:41.597 --> 34:43.703
Just keep trying.

34:44.382 --> 34:45.688
All right.

34:45.888 --> 34:49.858
♪♪ <i>Gary numan's "I am dust"
playing</i>...

34:51.645 --> 34:56.458
[ Engine revving ]

34:57.189 --> 35:00.849
♪ We all pray for the end ♪

35:01.189 --> 35:04.321
♪ for the God to take us ♪

35:04.954 --> 35:06.633
[ horns blare ]

35:06.765 --> 35:11.149
♪ We were falling down ♪

35:11.253 --> 35:13.253
♪ one by one ♪

35:13.568 --> 35:15.498
that had to be it.

35:16.352 --> 35:18.657
- ♪ We were weak ♪
- Boom.

35:18.748 --> 35:22.344
- ♪ And the fear ♪
- Holy shit. That looks good.

35:23.212 --> 35:24.719
Yeah.

35:25.121 --> 35:27.675
♪ We're here waiting for you ♪

35:28.344 --> 35:30.482
♪ we are yours ♪

35:30.530 --> 35:32.633
[ laughing ]

35:32.820 --> 35:34.797
Whoo!

35:35.056 --> 35:37.024
[ Engine revving ]

35:37.305 --> 35:38.587
[ Tires screech ]

35:38.635 --> 35:40.665
♪ Are yours ♪

35:40.872 --> 35:43.313
- Great job.
- Aah!

35:43.580 --> 35:45.480
♪♪

35:45.825 --> 35:47.888
(Man:) Hey, watch it!

35:48.885 --> 35:50.615
[ Exhales ]

35:50.725 --> 35:52.505
Man.
[ Laughter ]

35:54.741 --> 35:56.741
[ Coughs ]

35:56.872 --> 35:58.712
(Man:) Oh, he hit it hard.

35:58.833 --> 36:00.302
[ Groans ]

36:04.584 --> 36:06.747
[ Metal clanking ]

36:10.686 --> 36:12.356
[ Engine turns off ]

36:14.396 --> 36:16.232
(Baz:) Good job, man.

36:16.597 --> 36:17.864
[ Sniffs ]

36:18.020 --> 36:19.920
[ Sighs ]

36:22.372 --> 36:24.208
How bad?

36:24.708 --> 36:26.388
Oh, it's cool, man.
It's...

36:26.500 --> 36:27.853
[ mouth full ] No, no, no.

36:28.349 --> 36:29.676
Let's take a look at it.

36:29.849 --> 36:32.037
[ Blade clicks ]
[ Exhales sharply ]

36:33.232 --> 36:35.060
[ Groans ] There you go. You're good.
You're good.

36:35.107 --> 36:36.482
[ Exhales sharply ]

36:36.662 --> 36:39.152
[ Fabric rips ]
[ Groans ]

36:39.318 --> 36:42.365
[ Grunts ] Oh, shit.

36:43.849 --> 36:45.997
Take a look at that, man.

36:51.205 --> 36:53.540
Oh, shit. Yeah, that's bad.

36:53.723 --> 36:55.090
- I'll get the medical kit.
- Yeah.

36:55.303 --> 36:56.658
- W-W-What are you getting?
- What's...

36:56.705 --> 36:58.120
Well, we can't take you
to the hospital,

36:58.167 --> 36:59.954
so we're gonna have to deal
with it right here.

37:00.001 --> 37:01.470
What do you mean "deal with it"?

37:01.658 --> 37:03.876
We can cauterize it
or we can use a staple gun.

37:03.962 --> 37:05.790
- It's your choice.
- A staple gun?

37:05.884 --> 37:08.084
Yeah, it's a medical one.
You want me to decide for you?

37:08.138 --> 37:09.189
Give me this.

37:09.442 --> 37:11.869
I'd go with the soldering iron
if I were you.

37:12.181 --> 37:15.064
It's a little more painful,
but it doesn't scar as much.

37:15.136 --> 37:18.760
- Serious?
- Yeah. We'll hold you down.

37:19.250 --> 37:20.633
- [ Grunting ] Okay, just relax.
- You're all right.

37:20.681 --> 37:22.141
Relax. Relax.

37:22.502 --> 37:25.102
Ready?
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:25.236 --> 37:26.659
There you go.
[ Groans ]

37:26.767 --> 37:29.736
- Ah, no, no. Come on.
- Just... just give me a sec.

37:29.937 --> 37:33.140
[ Panting ]

37:33.251 --> 37:34.494
All right.

37:34.666 --> 37:36.096
All right. Just...

37:36.144 --> 37:37.392
- Staple gun.
- Staple gun!

37:37.440 --> 37:38.322
Staple gun.
I wanna go with the staple gun.

37:38.370 --> 37:40.650
- Good call, man.
- You're all right. All right.

37:41.392 --> 37:43.948
All right.
All right, hold him down.

37:44.220 --> 37:46.431
- Ready?
- [ Groans ]

37:49.857 --> 37:51.370
- All right, you ready? Here we go.
- You're all right, man. Come on.

37:51.417 --> 37:53.056
Here we go.
[ Grunts ]

37:54.103 --> 37:55.392
Aah!
[ Stapler clicks ]

37:55.483 --> 37:57.083
